-- Finmeccanica Said to Get $1.7 Billion Italian Air Force Helicopter Order
-- B y   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e   a n d   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2010-11-02T14:32:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/finmeccanica-said-to-get-1-7-billion-italian-air-force-helicopter-order.html
Finmeccanica SpA ’s AgustaWestland
unit received an order for 22 helicopters from Italy’s Air
Force, people familiar with the matter said.  The order is for 10 search-and-rescue AW139 helicopters and
12 combat AW101 helicopters, said the people, who asked not be
named before an official announcement. The order is valued at
about 1.2 billion euros ($1.7 billion), one person said. The
investment was approved on Oct. 13 by the Italian Senate’s
Defense Committee, according to the Italian Parliament’s
 website . Finmeccanica declined to comment.   The order was originally reported by Il Sole 24 Ore today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Bertacche at 
 mbertacche@bloomberg.net  